New Records: Namibia scored the highest total in a Super Over in a men's T20 World Cup competition with 21 runs
Key Match Events: Oman's fightback in the death overs went in vain
David Wiese's heroic efforts both with bat and ball in the Super Over helped Namibia win
Ruben Trumpelmann's pace attack jolted Oman, taking three wickets inside the powerplay
David Wiese excelled with the ball after being tasked with bowling the Super Over for Namibia, taking a wicket and giving only 10 runs
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game finished in a tie, marking the first Super Over in a men's T20 World Cup tournament since 2012
Namibia dropped critical catches, but eventually won the Super Over by 11 runs
Others: Bilal Khan gave Oman the perfect start, bowling opener Michael van Lingen for a duck off the very second ball of the innings
Zeeshan Maqsood held the innings together during the first powerplay, keeping Oman's innings steady and increasing the scoring rate to run a ball
